1
00:00:37,416 --> 00:00:40,840
[China]

2
00:01:32,136 --> 00:01:37,988
[Episode 1]
The Heart Sutra of the Great Wisdom.

3
00:01:37,988 --> 00:01:43,848
When practicing the perfection of wisdom,
he saw the five aggregates are all empty.

4
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:58,382
Three agents are dead.

5
00:01:58,382 --> 00:02:00,552
There is nowhere left to retreat.

6
00:02:00,552 --> 00:02:03,726
[National Security Advisor, Kwon Sun Bok]

7
00:02:03,726 --> 00:02:05,736
Let's call off the operation.

8
00:02:05,736 --> 00:02:09,512
[NIS Counterintelligence Team Leader,
Cho Seong Wo]

9
00:02:10,862 --> 00:02:14,600
We got intel that an NIS agent was working
with a North Korean officer to make drugs.

10
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:18,030
We built a six-month operation
based on that single lead.

11
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:19,336
And this is what it led to.

12
00:02:19,336 --> 00:02:22,926
Our job is to devote ourselves
in the shadows for the nation.

13
00:02:22,926 --> 00:02:26,568
Are we just going to sit back
and watch one rat eat away

14
00:02:26,568 --> 00:02:28,160
the country's treasury?

15
00:02:31,086 --> 00:02:32,968
That darn rat in the NIS.

16
00:02:32,968 --> 00:02:36,224
We should drag him in
and put him on trial for our men.

17
00:02:37,454 --> 00:02:39,584
Have you identified who it is?

18
00:02:47,912 --> 00:02:50,792
NIS Counterintelligence Division
First Deputy Director Han Kyung Wook.

19
00:02:50,792 --> 00:02:53,248
You know him well, right?

20
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:58,222
Why would a spy-hunting ace
be in bed with North Korea?

21
00:02:58,222 --> 00:02:59,528
Is this fake intel?

22
00:02:59,528 --> 00:03:01,992
This is intel bought with agents' lives.

23
00:03:01,992 --> 00:03:03,144
It's solid.

24
00:03:03,144 --> 00:03:06,120
Do you have solid evidence?

25
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:08,104
There is

26
00:03:08,104 --> 00:03:09,856
solid evidence.

27
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:16,968
<i>A few days ago, a North Korean operative
from the Counterintelligence Bureau,</i>

28
00:03:16,968 --> 00:03:19,624
<i>code-named Black Pearl, defected.</i>

29
00:03:19,624 --> 00:03:24,040
<i>While escaping, she stole a USB containing
slush funds of senior North Korean officials</i>

30
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,736
<i>and smuggling data.</i>

31
00:03:25,736 --> 00:03:28,776
<i>Inside it is information
about drug transactions</i>

32
00:03:28,776 --> 00:03:31,304
<i>between Han Kyung Wook
and a North Korean officer.</i>

33
00:03:31,304 --> 00:03:33,352
<i>Once we secure that USB,</i>

34
00:03:33,352 --> 00:03:37,064
<i>Han Kyung Wook will never get away.</i>

35
00:03:37,064 --> 00:03:41,032
<i>But, there's one problem.</i>

36
00:03:41,032 --> 00:03:45,832
<i>We tried contacting Black Pearl through
unofficial channels, but negotiations failed.</i>

37
00:03:45,832 --> 00:03:49,096
[Japanese Intelligence Agent,
Michiko Shibasaki]

38
00:03:50,728 --> 00:03:54,664
<i>Black Pearl's trying to sell that information</i>

39
00:03:54,664 --> 00:03:57,248
<i>to Japanese intelligence at a high price.</i>

40
00:03:59,528 --> 00:04:02,344
In two days, Black Pearl will sail to Japan.

41
00:04:02,344 --> 00:04:03,816
[Boarding Pass, Mokpo-Fukuoka]
The meeting with Japanese agents

42
00:04:03,816 --> 00:04:05,288
will take place on the ferry.

43
00:04:05,288 --> 00:04:06,696
We must intercept it before then.

44
00:04:06,696 --> 00:04:09,096
If we fail,

45
00:04:09,096 --> 00:04:12,744
is there another option?

46
00:04:12,744 --> 00:04:14,384
No.

47
00:04:18,504 --> 00:04:23,752
If we can't stop this, massive amounts
of drugs will flood into the country.

48
00:04:23,752 --> 00:04:27,392
Then it'll only be a matter of time
before Korea becomes a drug state.

49
00:04:29,256 --> 00:04:31,688
For this operation,

50
00:04:31,688 --> 00:04:35,432
we need someone
who will succeed no matter what.

51
00:04:35,432 --> 00:04:37,320
Jeez.

52
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:40,296
There is no one left we can trust with this.

53
00:04:40,296 --> 00:04:42,446
There is someone suitable.

54
00:04:42,446 --> 00:04:46,600
Do you know there's a unit inside NIS

55
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,928
that doesn't even exist
in any internal records?

56
00:04:51,755 --> 00:04:53,768
- This is good.
- Enjoy!

57
00:04:53,768 --> 00:04:55,592
Cheers!

58
00:04:55,592 --> 00:04:58,304
<i>There's only one agent in the department.</i>

59
00:05:00,296 --> 00:05:01,646
What's going on?

60
00:05:01,646 --> 00:05:06,088
<i>NIS's elite black-op agent, deployed
only when every other mission has failed.</i>

61
00:05:06,088 --> 00:05:07,820
Just get him.

62
00:05:43,368 --> 00:05:48,000
<i>Codename... Shadow.</i>

63
00:05:49,006 --> 00:05:50,888
Even if Shadow is deployed,

64
00:05:50,888 --> 00:05:53,288
there's still a risk of information leakage.

65
00:05:53,288 --> 00:05:56,328
Vice Director Han's faction holds
immense power within NIS.

66
00:05:56,328 --> 00:05:59,656
[Thousand-Buddha Hall]

67
00:05:59,656 --> 00:06:01,800
This operation

68
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:04,296
will be carried out under strict secrecy.

69
00:06:04,296 --> 00:06:08,136
Let's keep this between you, Shadow, and me.

70
00:06:09,992 --> 00:06:12,288
If this goes wrong,

71
00:06:13,512 --> 00:06:16,392
you could really be in danger.

72
00:06:17,352 --> 00:06:20,648
To bring down none other than Han Kyung Wook,

73
00:06:20,648 --> 00:06:22,976
I've got to put my neck on the line.

74
00:06:34,856 --> 00:06:36,968
It's unfortunate things turned out this way.

75
00:06:36,968 --> 00:06:39,752
I didn't even expect
Black Pearl to act like this.

76
00:06:39,752 --> 00:06:42,408
So what's the solution?

77
00:06:42,408 --> 00:06:45,064
[NIS First Deputy Director, Han Kyung Wook]

78
00:06:45,064 --> 00:06:49,096
We'll use Yanbian thugs to clean this up.

79
00:06:49,096 --> 00:06:52,392
[Ministry of People's Armed Forces Major,
Lee Cheol Jin]

80
00:06:52,392 --> 00:06:55,432
Shadow, who will be deployed
for this operation,

81
00:06:55,432 --> 00:06:57,704
he's a monster nurtured by NIS.

82
00:06:57,704 --> 00:07:02,216
Even a whole truckload
of amateurs won't be enough.

83
00:07:02,216 --> 00:07:04,136
Monster against monster.

84
00:07:04,136 --> 00:07:09,576
How about deploying our top agent
skilled in South Korean operations?

85
00:07:09,576 --> 00:07:11,808
The top agent?

86
00:07:19,496 --> 00:07:20,776
<i>Bulgae.</i>

87
00:07:20,776 --> 00:07:23,816
<i>He's skilled in disguise
and a master of Taekkyon.</i>

88
00:07:23,816 --> 00:07:25,960
<i>So he moves like a ghost.</i>

89
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:29,504
<i>Weak South Korean punks stand no chance.</i>

90
00:07:51,016 --> 00:07:54,720
<i>I've never seen anyone who can handle Bulgae.</i>

91
00:07:56,206 --> 00:07:58,598
<i>Trust him to handle it.</i>

92
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:06,496
We need a safety measure.

93
00:08:07,208 --> 00:08:09,888
Let's go with a two-pronged operation.

94
00:08:11,182 --> 00:08:13,318
This is interesting.

95
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:45,608
[Boss of the Hwasan faction, Hwang Hwa San]

96
00:08:47,246 --> 00:08:52,776
You didn't come to talk about
the dusty old past, did you?

97
00:08:53,512 --> 00:08:56,040
So what's your business?

98
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,120
Still sharp at reading situations, I see.

99
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:00,680
It's been a while.
Let's do this job together.

100
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:01,832
Who is it?

101
00:09:01,832 --> 00:09:06,720
The man who can make even Mr. Han this tense?

102
00:09:09,416 --> 00:09:11,656
Don't cross the line.

103
00:09:11,656 --> 00:09:13,864
Get me someone capable for this task.

104
00:09:13,864 --> 00:09:16,136
Not those petty thugs.

105
00:09:16,136 --> 00:09:18,176
Get me someone solid.

106
00:09:19,304 --> 00:09:22,496
Someone solid?

107
00:09:26,024 --> 00:09:29,451
I've got one guy under me like that.

108
00:09:39,272 --> 00:09:44,648
<i>A true fighter who brought down
nationwide gangsters armed with nothing</i>

109
00:09:44,648 --> 00:09:47,136
<i>but his bare hands.</i>

110
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:51,272
<i>No matter who the opponent is,</i>

111
00:09:51,272 --> 00:09:58,048
<i>one punch from him will settle it cleanly.</i>

112
00:10:41,672 --> 00:10:45,448
<i>The item contains our Republic's
top-secret documents.</i>

113
00:10:45,448 --> 00:10:48,680
<i>We can't let the South Korean punks
take it away, can we?</i>

114
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:53,568
An agent codenamed Shadow
has already been deployed in South Korea.

115
00:10:54,350 --> 00:11:00,262
<i>Rumor says that punk is the best operative
in the South, so be careful.</i>

116
00:11:01,198 --> 00:11:04,614
We have to secure the item before he does.

117
00:11:09,416 --> 00:11:13,128
<i>Beom Ryong, what kind of organization
is our Hwasan faction?</i>

118
00:11:13,128 --> 00:11:17,992
<i>Wasn't it the one we built
from nothing in Gangnam with our fists?</i>

119
00:11:17,992 --> 00:11:21,096
Even though we took orders
from Han Kyung Wook,

120
00:11:21,096 --> 00:11:26,536
he's the kind of guy who could
stab our organization in the back one day.

121
00:11:26,536 --> 00:11:31,432
We can't stake our organization's fate
on someone like that.

122
00:11:31,432 --> 00:11:34,952
<i>So whether it's the NIS or North Korea,</i>

123
00:11:34,952 --> 00:11:40,512
<i>you must secure the item first,
no matter what.</i>

124
00:11:44,424 --> 00:11:46,408
<i>Ho Myung,</i>

125
00:11:46,408 --> 00:11:49,288
<i>Han Kyung Wook has influence
not only in the NIS</i>

126
00:11:49,288 --> 00:11:50,760
<i>but also in the prosecution and politics.</i>

127
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:54,016
<i>If we leave him be like this, his misdeeds</i>

128
00:11:54,856 --> 00:11:57,288
<i>might be buried forever.</i>

129
00:11:57,288 --> 00:12:00,832
This is our last chance to take him down.

130
00:12:02,062 --> 00:12:05,486
And there's talk that Bulgae
will be deployed this time.

131
00:12:05,486 --> 00:12:07,240
<i>Watch yourself out there.</i>

132
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:10,760
You only focus on securing the item.

133
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:12,576
<i>Understood?</i>

134
00:12:47,816 --> 00:12:49,832
<i>This mission</i>

135
00:12:49,832 --> 00:12:52,384
<i>will be your final mission as Shadow.</i>

136
00:13:48,296 --> 00:13:51,776
[NIS First Deputy Director, Han Kyung Wook]

137
00:13:59,534 --> 00:14:00,686
What is the operation status?

138
00:14:00,686 --> 00:14:01,992
<i>Something went wrong.</i>

139
00:14:01,992 --> 00:14:04,328
<i>We failed to secure the item.</i>

140
00:14:04,328 --> 00:14:05,672
Did Jeong Ho Myung take it?

141
00:14:05,672 --> 00:14:08,008
<i>No, a North Korean agent took it,</i>

142
00:14:08,008 --> 00:14:10,728
<i>but the whereabouts are unknown
along with the item.</i>

143
00:14:10,728 --> 00:14:12,248
Erase all traces cleanly.

144
00:14:12,248 --> 00:14:13,704
As for the missing item,

145
00:14:13,704 --> 00:14:16,640
recover it by any means necessary.

146
00:14:20,014 --> 00:14:23,392
Oh, yeah, Mr. Cho.
What is the operation status?

147
00:14:26,952 --> 00:14:29,512
Get to safety first.

148
00:14:29,512 --> 00:14:32,112
Let's meet at the safe house.

149
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,760
About the GPS you attached to the bag,

150
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:50,024
that punk Bulgae's last signal was
picked up on Yeongseondo Island.

151
00:14:50,024 --> 00:14:51,528
Now that the operation's gone wrong,

152
00:14:51,528 --> 00:14:53,032
Han Kyung Wook won't stand still.

153
00:14:53,032 --> 00:14:55,032
All records about you have been erased.

154
00:14:55,032 --> 00:14:57,640
Go to Yeongseondo Island
and just find Bulgae, got it?

155
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:59,784
Find Bulgae no matter what.

156
00:14:59,784 --> 00:15:01,080
No, don't come!

157
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,376
<i>Don't come!</i>

158
00:15:02,376 --> 00:15:04,680
<i>Don't come and stay hidden
until I contact you, got it?</i>

159
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,688
<i>I'll reach out.</i>

160
00:15:08,872 --> 00:15:10,182
Seong Wo.

161
00:15:13,224 --> 00:15:15,040
Seong Wo?

162
00:15:16,328 --> 00:15:20,000
Seong Wo!

163
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:34,856
[10 Years Later]

164
00:15:34,856 --> 00:15:38,760
[2026, Yeongseondo Island]

165
00:15:46,856 --> 00:15:49,160
Pardon?

166
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,312
What did you say?

167
00:15:50,312 --> 00:15:52,312
You're going through menopause.

168
00:15:52,312 --> 00:15:55,592
You've heard of menopause, right?

169
00:15:55,592 --> 00:15:56,824
Does menopause

170
00:15:56,824 --> 00:15:58,568
happen to men too?

171
00:15:58,568 --> 00:16:02,440
It often occurs in middle-aged men
with decreased testosterone.

172
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:04,608
Well...

173
00:16:05,230 --> 00:16:07,278
there seems to be some misunderstanding,
so let's go over it again.

174
00:16:07,278 --> 00:16:12,776
Your testosterone levels
are currently below the threshold.

175
00:16:12,776 --> 00:16:14,920
I'll prescribe male hormone medication first.

176
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:17,416
Take it consistently,
and we'll monitor your progress.

177
00:16:17,416 --> 00:16:18,760
Hormone medication?

178
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:23,232
If left untreated,
the symptoms will get worse.

179
00:16:23,848 --> 00:16:27,048
What kind of symptoms?

180
00:16:27,048 --> 00:16:29,416
Fatigue, lethargy,

181
00:16:29,416 --> 00:16:31,616
reduced sexual function,

182
00:16:32,424 --> 00:16:35,040
and even possible height loss.

183
00:16:40,808 --> 00:16:45,704
You are now ten years in the past.

184
00:16:45,704 --> 00:16:49,056
What do you see in front of you?

185
00:16:51,624 --> 00:16:53,000
People...

186
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:57,568
What are you and those people doing,
Jae Soon?

187
00:16:58,472 --> 00:17:00,872
Fighting 17 to 1.

188
00:17:00,872 --> 00:17:03,784
They're no match for me at all.

189
00:17:03,784 --> 00:17:07,432
Uh, n-no... I...

190
00:17:07,432 --> 00:17:09,728
Open your eyes!

191
00:17:15,886 --> 00:17:20,868
It's so clear. Are my memories coming back?

192
00:17:21,806 --> 00:17:25,102
I told you to stop watching action movies.

193
00:17:25,102 --> 00:17:28,262
You're always thinking about
infiltrations and defusing bombs.

194
00:17:28,262 --> 00:17:32,168
That's why you keep failing at hypnosis.

195
00:17:32,168 --> 00:17:33,384
I haven't watched any action movies.

196
00:17:33,384 --> 00:17:35,984
Looks like the hypnotherapy isn't working.

197
00:17:46,824 --> 00:17:48,296
Did you gain weight?

198
00:17:48,296 --> 00:17:51,072
You look good.

199
00:17:53,384 --> 00:17:55,624
Me? Well...

200
00:17:55,624 --> 00:17:58,318
How's your health, though?

201
00:17:58,318 --> 00:18:00,392
I heard you suffered from the flu recently.

202
00:18:00,392 --> 00:18:04,456
Yeah, I bought thermal underwear
with the money you sent,

203
00:18:04,456 --> 00:18:06,304
and I'm all better now.

204
00:18:06,990 --> 00:18:11,238
But what about the item? Any news yet?

205
00:18:12,494 --> 00:18:14,798
I'm sorry. I'm not good enough.

206
00:18:14,798 --> 00:18:19,168
But I'm still searching thoroughly,
so I'm sure we'll have good news soon.

207
00:18:22,318 --> 00:18:25,288
[The Holy Bible]
The Lord said,

208
00:18:25,288 --> 00:18:27,656
"Knock, and the door will be
opened to those who knock."

209
00:18:27,656 --> 00:18:29,416
Keep knocking until it opens.

210
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:31,240
Keep knocking, and don't give up.

211
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:33,326
Amen!

212
00:18:33,326 --> 00:18:35,816
[JUMBO24]

213
00:18:41,928 --> 00:18:43,680
Seoraksan Mountain!

214
00:18:44,744 --> 00:18:46,760
Seoraksan Mountain is in Gangwon-do Province.

215
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,200
This is Yeongseondo Island.

216
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:51,336
Are you trying to play
word games with me right now?

217
00:18:51,336 --> 00:18:54,432
I mean a cigarette.
Give me a Seoraksan cigarette!

218
00:18:55,688 --> 00:18:58,920
No one asks for that cigarette
except you, sir,

219
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,840
so we have no plans to stock them.

220
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:03,720
I've told you several times.
Why haven't you stocked them?

221
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,440
You...

222
00:19:07,464 --> 00:19:09,416
Don't you know who I am?

223
00:19:09,416 --> 00:19:10,440
Who are you?

224
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:11,624
I have no idea who you are.

225
00:19:11,624 --> 00:19:15,144
- Oh my, I can't just hit a civilian...
- Go ahead, hit me.

226
00:19:15,144 --> 00:19:17,744
I'm tired of this too!

227
00:19:18,472 --> 00:19:19,912
Look at this punk.

228
00:19:19,912 --> 00:19:21,384
Good, you picked

229
00:19:21,384 --> 00:19:24,552
- the wrong day.
- Think only you can take your clothes off?

230
00:19:24,552 --> 00:19:28,200
I can do it too!

231
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,888
Sir!

232
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:36,078
Jeez...

233
00:19:36,078 --> 00:19:37,198
Mr. Bong!

234
00:19:37,198 --> 00:19:38,280
Oh, yes.

235
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:40,968
Mr. Bong, the bathroom is completely clogged!

236
00:19:40,968 --> 00:19:42,024
Yes.

237
00:19:42,024 --> 00:19:43,688
Mr. Bong!

238
00:19:43,688 --> 00:19:45,992
The printer is down again.

239
00:19:45,992 --> 00:19:47,888
Hurry!

240
00:19:53,544 --> 00:19:56,168
Mr. Bong,

241
00:19:56,168 --> 00:19:59,144
if you stay here, am I supposed to
handle the rebar receiving alone?

242
00:19:59,144 --> 00:20:03,488
Well, the printer is broken, so...

243
00:20:04,494 --> 00:20:05,896
[A fun and lively workplace]

244
00:20:17,512 --> 00:20:20,104
Oh, you fixed it, Ms. Lee.

245
00:20:20,104 --> 00:20:23,112
Thanks.

246
00:20:23,112 --> 00:20:28,264
Mr. Bong, I've been meaning to tell you.

247
00:20:28,264 --> 00:20:31,240
You should decline tasks
that aren't your job.

248
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:34,216
If you keep giving in like this,
they'll just take advantage of you more.

249
00:20:34,216 --> 00:20:37,952
You're right. I got it.
Next time I'll refuse firmly.

250
00:20:38,632 --> 00:20:39,880
Go on, hurry.

251
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:42,056
Mr. Bong!

252
00:20:42,056 --> 00:20:43,976
Sorry,

253
00:20:43,976 --> 00:20:47,392
but I'm a bit busy right now.

254
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:51,328
I didn't hear that wrong, did I?

255
00:20:52,936 --> 00:20:54,624
You're busy?

256
00:20:59,208 --> 00:21:03,328
Even if you're busy,
please handle the car wash.

257
00:21:12,072 --> 00:21:15,296
Uh, nice ball!

258
00:21:15,976 --> 00:21:18,144
Sir.

259
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:30,664
Oh, that's a dead ball!
Your speed was amazing, though.

260
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:36,776
Oh, sorry! I've got strong arms,
so my control is off.

261
00:21:36,776 --> 00:21:39,376
Oh, goodness.

262
00:21:42,056 --> 00:21:43,880
Mr. Bong!

263
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:46,312
It's not shining.

264
00:21:46,312 --> 00:21:48,312
Are you slacking off?

265
00:21:48,312 --> 00:21:50,312
I'm sorry.

266
00:21:50,312 --> 00:21:54,984
Anyway, you just can't
seem to do anything properly.

267
00:21:54,984 --> 00:21:59,848
Well, what can I expect from someone
who doesn't even remember what he used to do?

268
00:21:59,848 --> 00:22:02,152
What a fool.

269
00:22:02,152 --> 00:22:06,856
Only I would take in someone
old and flawed like him.

270
00:22:06,856 --> 00:22:09,456
Does he even know anything? My foot.

271
00:22:10,888 --> 00:22:12,800
Sir!

272
00:22:14,062 --> 00:22:16,006
What?

273
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:22,350
Which side should I polish?

274
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:25,384
You seriously don't know that?

275
00:22:25,384 --> 00:22:28,808
The hood, of course, the hood!

276
00:22:28,808 --> 00:22:31,104
Oh, my.

277
00:22:47,528 --> 00:22:49,608
Mr. Kim! Please take their order.

278
00:22:49,608 --> 00:22:51,272
Understood.

279
00:22:51,272 --> 00:22:53,872
Yes, understood.

280
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:05,864
Why are you so late?

281
00:23:05,864 --> 00:23:08,296
Why are only you and him here, Father?

282
00:23:08,296 --> 00:23:09,487
Where is Ji Woo's mom?

283
00:23:09,487 --> 00:23:12,950
She suddenly left for her dance club today.

284
00:23:12,950 --> 00:23:14,679
Again?

285
00:23:14,679 --> 00:23:15,768
Has she caught the dancing bug or something?

286
00:23:15,768 --> 00:23:16,890
What's gotten into her lately?

287
00:23:16,890 --> 00:23:19,170
You live with her. How am I supposed to know?

288
00:23:19,170 --> 00:23:20,392
Hey, Mr. Jeong, orders are piling up.

289
00:23:20,392 --> 00:23:21,824
- Hurry and get in, get in.
- Yeah, quickly.

290
00:23:21,824 --> 00:23:23,010
Hurry up and clean this up too.

291
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:24,852
Over there! Yeah, yeah.

292
00:23:55,910 --> 00:23:58,600
[Friendly Convenience Store,
Yeongseondo Island Branch Wins Award!]

293
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:03,624
[Spicy Pork Lunchbox]

294
00:24:04,968 --> 00:24:07,032
Jeez.

295
00:24:07,032 --> 00:24:10,144
I'm sick of these expired lunchboxes.

296
00:24:14,239 --> 00:24:17,048
Hey, you're just cranky
because you're hungry.

297
00:24:20,540 --> 00:24:23,288
Is this the first time
that old man's acted like that?

298
00:24:23,288 --> 00:24:25,310
Can't you just let it go nicely?

299
00:24:26,176 --> 00:24:27,688
[Friendly Convenience Store]
We must maintain

300
00:24:27,688 --> 00:24:29,650
[Yeongseondo Island Branch Wins Award!]
the kind convenience store reputation!

301
00:24:32,296 --> 00:24:34,120
Ugh.

302
00:24:35,420 --> 00:24:38,352
I can't live like this anymore.

303
00:24:38,352 --> 00:24:41,290
Let's quickly find the item
and leave Yeongseondo Island.

304
00:24:41,290 --> 00:24:43,228
I was wondering when you'd say that.

305
00:24:43,228 --> 00:24:46,830
If finding that item were so easy,
why would I be sitting here like this?

306
00:24:46,830 --> 00:24:49,800
What was our original goal
coming to this island?

307
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:53,394
To take down NIS agent Jeong Ho Myung
who's searching for the item, wasn't it?

308
00:24:54,888 --> 00:24:56,542
Look at this.

309
00:24:56,542 --> 00:24:58,472
Jeong Ho Myung looks more lively these days,

310
00:24:58,472 --> 00:24:59,972
and his actions seem unusual.

311
00:24:59,972 --> 00:25:01,630
It feels like he's about to make a move.

312
00:25:01,630 --> 00:25:04,725
Are you still tailing the people
at O Ran Chinese Restaurant these days?

313
00:25:04,725 --> 00:25:06,268
Yeah, well, sometimes.

314
00:25:06,268 --> 00:25:08,771
Because that's my job.

315
00:25:08,771 --> 00:25:13,992
Jeong Ho Myung's married and living happily.
Why would he go looking for that item?

316
00:25:13,992 --> 00:25:17,697
Instead of chasing him, think about
increasing our sales!

317
00:25:17,697 --> 00:25:21,251
I'm already stretched thin
taking care of big boss in prison.

318
00:25:21,251 --> 00:25:22,850
Does he think the same way?

319
00:25:22,850 --> 00:25:24,520
Yeah!

320
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:28,209
That we should forget revenge
and just focus on supporting him in prison?

321
00:25:28,209 --> 00:25:30,068
I'm sure that's what he thinks!

322
00:25:32,005 --> 00:25:34,291
Whatever he thinks,

323
00:25:34,291 --> 00:25:36,674
I can't live
as a convenience store clerk anymore!

324
00:25:39,148 --> 00:25:41,051
What are you gonna do about it?

325
00:25:43,684 --> 00:25:45,800
Come on!

326
00:25:49,992 --> 00:25:51,208
[Welcome; Break Time]

327
00:25:51,208 --> 00:25:55,954
[Community-Built Safe School Routes]
<i>Yes, one large sweet and sour pork...</i>

328
00:25:56,840 --> 00:25:58,024
<i>Moving on to the next news.</i>

329
00:25:58,024 --> 00:26:00,616
<i>As the Imcheon mayoral election nears,</i>

330
00:26:00,616 --> 00:26:03,834
<i>independent candidate Kim Seon Jung
and Saehanjin Party candidate Han Kyung Wook</i>

331
00:26:03,834 --> 00:26:07,080
<i>are holding intense
campaign rallies across Imcheon City.</i>

332
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:09,960
<i>Reporter Kim Yi Young
visited the heated scene.</i>

333
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:16,840
<i>The path to making Imcheon
the happiest city in South Korea!</i>

334
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:19,240
<i>I, Kim Seon Jung,</i>

335
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:22,248
<i>will move forward with the citizens</i>

336
00:26:22,248 --> 00:26:24,456
[Kim Seon Jung, independent candidate]
<i>of Imcheon City!</i>

337
00:26:24,456 --> 00:26:28,168
<i>- Kim Seon Jung!</i>
<i>- Kim Seon Jung!</i>

338
00:26:28,168 --> 00:26:32,584
[Han Kyung Wook, Saehanjin Party candidate]
<i>Please trust number 2, Han Kyung Wook.</i>

339
00:26:32,584 --> 00:26:36,520
<i>If I, Han Kyung Wook,
am elected as Imcheon City mayor,</i>

340
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:39,464
[Han Kyung Wook, Saehanjin Party candidate]
<i>I will develop a large-scale</i>

341
00:26:39,464 --> 00:26:41,128
<i>integrated tourism complex</i>

342
00:26:41,128 --> 00:26:45,984
<i>to turn Yeongseondo Island
into one of Korea's top tourist destinations.</i>

343
00:26:46,888 --> 00:26:51,816
<i>- Han Kyung Wook!</i>
<i>- Han Kyung Wook!</i>

344
00:26:51,816 --> 00:26:58,624
<i>- Number 2.</i>
<i>- Han Kyung Wook!</i>

345
00:27:01,270 --> 00:27:03,510
Why did you turn it off? I was watching that.

346
00:27:03,510 --> 00:27:04,520
It's noisy.

347
00:27:04,520 --> 00:27:07,750
Do you know how important this election is
for Yeongseondo Island?

348
00:27:07,750 --> 00:27:09,290
Jeez.

349
00:27:09,290 --> 00:27:14,528
Han Kyung Wook must win,
then Kim Seon Jung shows up out of nowhere.

350
00:27:15,208 --> 00:27:16,936
Why does it have to be Han Kyung Wook?

351
00:27:16,936 --> 00:27:20,072
I've been a deliveryman for 20 years.

352
00:27:20,072 --> 00:27:22,792
I can tell just by looking at someone

353
00:27:22,792 --> 00:27:25,000
whether they'll ask for freebies
or skip payment.

354
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,430
But look at Kim Seon Jung.

355
00:27:26,430 --> 00:27:30,784
Do you think a lifelong teacher
can really do politics?

356
00:27:33,128 --> 00:27:37,930
But Han Kyung Wook
has a completely different aura.

357
00:27:37,930 --> 00:27:40,168
He's a former NIS agent
and a two-term congressman.

358
00:27:40,168 --> 00:27:44,360
If Han Kyung Wook gets elected
and makes Yeongseondo Island a tourist zone,

359
00:27:44,360 --> 00:27:46,504
this place will skyrocket.

360
00:27:46,504 --> 00:27:49,352
Stop with the useless chatter, okay?

361
00:27:49,352 --> 00:27:51,080
Ho Myung.

362
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:52,808
Go do a delivery.

363
00:27:52,808 --> 00:27:54,630
Mr. Kim should go.

364
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:56,168
I need to prepare for dinner service.

365
00:27:56,168 --> 00:27:58,850
That's a place Mr. Kim can't go.

366
00:27:58,850 --> 00:28:00,832
Is there a place I can't go?

367
00:28:02,536 --> 00:28:03,656
Heaven Capital?

368
00:28:03,656 --> 00:28:08,488
Yeah, the place where you
always leave unpaid tabs.

369
00:28:08,488 --> 00:28:10,290
Oh dear, leaving tabs?

370
00:28:10,290 --> 00:28:11,656
With 20 years of delivery experience?

371
00:28:11,656 --> 00:28:13,000
Well...

372
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:16,904
While you're there,
collect the overdue credit, Ho Myung.

373
00:28:16,904 --> 00:28:20,710
Today's the day O Ran checks the ledger.
Look at the sales gap.

374
00:28:20,710 --> 00:28:21,960
Do you think she'll just let it slide?

375
00:28:23,830 --> 00:28:25,896
Do you really think Mr. Jeong
can collect from them?

376
00:28:25,896 --> 00:28:28,872
No way. I'll eat my hat if that happens.

377
00:28:28,872 --> 00:28:29,992
You.

378
00:28:29,992 --> 00:28:33,184
[Heaven Capital's order]
You should've lost at least 90 times by now.

379
00:28:34,248 --> 00:28:36,104
[Imcheon City]

380
00:28:36,104 --> 00:28:40,360
Why is the prosecution revisiting a case
that was already closed as a suicide?

381
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:44,392
Didn't Prosecutor Park say he'd handle it
without any problems, all confidently?

382
00:28:44,392 --> 00:28:48,008
Mr. Park got promoted to headquarters,
and someone new came in.

383
00:28:48,008 --> 00:28:51,432
They say that prosecutor is making a fuss,
insisting on going to the scene herself.

384
00:28:51,432 --> 00:28:52,936
The new prosecutor?

385
00:28:52,936 --> 00:28:55,912
Could she have caught on to something?

386
00:28:55,912 --> 00:28:58,504
You need something to even catch on to.

387
00:28:58,504 --> 00:29:00,310
What can she do now?

388
00:29:02,504 --> 00:29:04,392
But don't let your guard down.

389
00:29:04,392 --> 00:29:06,472
Do you know the prosecutor's nickname?

390
00:29:06,472 --> 00:29:08,072
What is it?

391
00:29:08,072 --> 00:29:09,530
They call her "Nongae."

392
00:29:09,530 --> 00:29:10,750
You know "Nongae," right?

393
00:29:10,750 --> 00:29:13,384
The courtesan who jumped into the river
dragging a Japanese general down with her.

394
00:29:13,384 --> 00:29:16,456
Once she takes on a case,
it's a fight to the death.

395
00:29:16,456 --> 00:29:19,880
She graduated from the police academy,
worked in violent crimes for a long time,

396
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:22,152
and was famous there as a complete maniac.

397
00:29:22,152 --> 00:29:24,712
Even after becoming a prosecutor,
she couldn't change her ways.

398
00:29:24,712 --> 00:29:27,432
Rumor has it she was reassigned to Imcheon

399
00:29:27,432 --> 00:29:29,800
for pursuing a sexual harassment case
against her superiors.

400
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:32,412
That's not a rumor, it's a fact.

401
00:29:32,412 --> 00:29:35,560
Hello, I'm Prosecutor Kang Young Ae

402
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:36,750
from the Imcheon District
Prosecutors' Office.

403
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:38,030
Nice to meet you!

404
00:29:38,030 --> 00:29:39,400
- Yes, nice to meet you.
- Yes.

405
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:40,840
I'm sorry, I...

406
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:42,152
I wasn't talking behind your back.

407
00:29:42,152 --> 00:29:46,184
No, no. Why are you
apologizing for stating facts?

408
00:29:46,184 --> 00:29:48,050
Let's go upstairs.

409
00:29:49,992 --> 00:29:51,750
Aren't you busy?

410
00:29:53,096 --> 00:29:57,490
Ms. Kang!

411
00:29:57,490 --> 00:29:59,528
[O Ran Chinese Restaurant]
Chairman Do, step down!

412
00:29:59,528 --> 00:30:01,192
Step down! Step down!

413
00:30:01,192 --> 00:30:03,592
[Break free from a gambling economy!]
The casino is ruining Yeongseondo Island.

414
00:30:03,592 --> 00:30:06,408
- Step down!
- Step down! Step down!

415
00:30:06,408 --> 00:30:09,416
Chairman Do of Heaven Casino
must withdraw immediately!

416
00:30:09,416 --> 00:30:12,136
[Break free from a gambling economy!]
Withdraw! Withdraw!

417
00:30:12,136 --> 00:30:15,656
Gambling industries exploiting
island residents, withdraw!

418
00:30:15,656 --> 00:30:18,024
Withdraw! Withdraw!

419
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:22,336
A casino in pristine Yeongseondo Island?
What nonsense is that!

420
00:30:50,523 --> 00:30:52,744
Oh, no.

421
00:30:52,744 --> 00:30:54,120
Oh, jeez.

422
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:58,048
I said don't do it.

423
00:31:20,104 --> 00:31:22,656
[Heaven Capital]

424
00:31:23,656 --> 00:31:26,792
Darn it, I want to go to heaven too!

425
00:31:26,792 --> 00:31:28,968
Hey, let's play one more round.

426
00:31:28,968 --> 00:31:31,744
You crazy, I've used it all.

427
00:31:32,648 --> 00:31:34,952
We need to go to heaven.

428
00:31:34,952 --> 00:31:36,250
We can go.

429
00:31:36,250 --> 00:31:40,544
[Heaven Capital, Nationwide Lowest Rates!]
Hey, don't. No, what the... This isn't right.

430
00:31:42,504 --> 00:31:45,512
How much do we take off the top?
Look, he even did it like this.

431
00:31:45,512 --> 00:31:48,488
- He took his cut like this.
- Delivery's here.

432
00:31:48,488 --> 00:31:50,432
Hey, come here. Over here.

433
00:31:51,048 --> 00:31:52,936
Here you go.

434
00:31:52,936 --> 00:31:56,224
Yes, thank you.

435
00:31:58,040 --> 00:31:59,808
This is 90 million won.

436
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:05,990
Hey, jjajang noodles are here, let's eat.

437
00:32:05,990 --> 00:32:07,944
- Yes!
- Yes!

438
00:32:07,944 --> 00:32:09,984
- Clean this up.
- Yes!

439
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:14,980
What's up?

440
00:32:14,980 --> 00:32:18,880
Including the ordered food,
the outstanding balance is 578,000 won.

441
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:20,616
Let's square things up first.

442
00:32:20,616 --> 00:32:22,920
Jeez, you're ruining my appetite.

443
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:25,832
We don't have any money.
Just put it on my tab.

444
00:32:25,832 --> 00:32:29,216
Then what's over there?
Just paper, not money?

445
00:32:30,189 --> 00:32:32,370
Darn it.

446
00:32:32,370 --> 00:32:33,890
You punk, seriously...

447
00:32:33,890 --> 00:32:35,208
Do you know what kind of money that is?

448
00:32:35,208 --> 00:32:38,176
If even one of those goes missing,
this place will turn into chaos.

449
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:42,080
I'll pay next time, just leave. Okay?

450
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:49,520
This punk doesn't understand a word.

451
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:53,248
Do you want to get beaten
until your ears ring?

452
00:33:02,890 --> 00:33:05,280
What are you doing? Darn it!

453
00:33:14,840 --> 00:33:16,992
Jeez.

454
00:33:19,592 --> 00:33:22,408
Darn it. You're nothing special.

455
00:33:22,408 --> 00:33:23,810
Just acting tough.

456
00:33:23,810 --> 00:33:29,192
If you don't settle next time,
we won't deliver.

457
00:33:29,192 --> 00:33:32,490
Bring more pickled radish
next time, you punk.

458
00:33:32,490 --> 00:33:34,536
And bring some fried dumplings on the house.

459
00:33:34,536 --> 00:33:35,688
- We're regulars.
- Hey, don't talk down to him.

460
00:33:35,688 --> 00:33:38,792
Up close, he seems older.

461
00:33:38,792 --> 00:33:40,232
Show respect, call him bro.

462
00:33:40,232 --> 00:33:41,608
Thank you, bro!

463
00:33:41,608 --> 00:33:43,752
Please give us more freebies next time!

464
00:33:43,752 --> 00:33:45,672
Bring it here, please.

465
00:33:45,672 --> 00:33:48,320
You punk, you get only half of it.

466
00:34:02,024 --> 00:34:07,176
<i>As if avoiding outside exposure,
newspapers are layered over the windows.</i>

467
00:34:07,176 --> 00:34:10,840
<i>The room is neatly organized,
as if ready to leave at any moment.</i>

468
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:15,527
Excuse me, but, ma'am, this case
has already been concluded as a suicide.

469
00:34:15,527 --> 00:34:18,848
Do you really need to look into it again?

470
00:34:23,623 --> 00:34:25,800
Why

471
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,496
are you so sure it was suicide?

472
00:34:27,496 --> 00:34:28,679
Why?

473
00:34:28,679 --> 00:34:30,376
Well, you see,

474
00:34:30,376 --> 00:34:32,808
isn't it obvious?

475
00:34:32,808 --> 00:34:36,719
A woman living alone doesn't meet anyone.

476
00:34:36,719 --> 00:34:39,272
Suffered from depression and hung herself.

477
00:34:39,272 --> 00:34:42,540
There's no need for a briefing on this case.

478
00:34:42,540 --> 00:34:46,504
<i>Based on the scene, it looks like a planned
suicide due to depression,</i>

479
00:34:46,504 --> 00:34:48,320
<i>as the detectives said.</i>

480
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:49,576
<i>But</i>

481
00:34:49,576 --> 00:34:51,784
<i>as someone who had been thinking
about death all this time,</i>

482
00:34:51,784 --> 00:34:54,376
<i>she didn't leave a suicide note at all?</i>

483
00:34:54,376 --> 00:34:57,536
<i>And she suddenly did it while washing dishes?</i>

484
00:35:11,304 --> 00:35:13,416
Well,

485
00:35:13,416 --> 00:35:16,328
if you've glanced over it,
let's leave it at that.

486
00:35:16,328 --> 00:35:17,910
We have to get going.

487
00:35:17,910 --> 00:35:20,168
<i>The detectives' reactions are odd too.</i>

488
00:35:20,168 --> 00:35:24,488
<i>It's just a simple suicide,
yet they're overly cautious around me.</i>

489
00:35:24,488 --> 00:35:29,056
You said she got into a noise dispute
with the neighbor upstairs, right?

490
00:35:31,410 --> 00:35:33,320
That's correct.

491
00:35:33,320 --> 00:35:36,520
Even a little noise, and she'd come up

492
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:40,256
screaming at me while I was on air,
and making a scene.

493
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:45,064
You must have argued often.

494
00:35:45,064 --> 00:35:46,536
Are you suspecting me?

495
00:35:46,536 --> 00:35:48,616
Do you know what kind of woman she is?

496
00:35:48,616 --> 00:35:52,170
One, two, three, four!

497
00:35:52,170 --> 00:35:54,632
[On Air]
Wave, wave, wave.

498
00:35:54,632 --> 00:35:56,188
Come on, jump!

499
00:36:00,936 --> 00:36:02,344
Darn it.

500
00:36:02,344 --> 00:36:04,168
Wait a moment, everyone.

501
00:36:04,168 --> 00:36:05,952
Come on.

502
00:36:05,952 --> 00:36:07,432
Who is it?

503
00:36:10,088 --> 00:36:11,144
[Exciting music for exercising]

504
00:36:12,008 --> 00:36:14,920
I told you if you make that banging noise
again, I won't let it slide!

505
00:36:14,920 --> 00:36:16,008
What are you doing?

506
00:36:16,008 --> 00:36:18,080
We're live right now!

507
00:36:18,824 --> 00:36:20,584
Whoa, no!

508
00:36:21,448 --> 00:36:23,784
What are you doing? Stop her quickly!

509
00:36:23,784 --> 00:36:25,768
- What are you doing?
- Hey, lady!

510
00:36:25,768 --> 00:36:27,496
What's wrong with you?

511
00:36:27,496 --> 00:36:28,920
Are you alright?

512
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:32,552
Darn it... Hey, lady!

513
00:36:33,256 --> 00:36:34,428
Hey!

514
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:46,568
Still, if I lift more than 5kg,

515
00:36:46,568 --> 00:36:48,840
my right shoulder feels like
it's going to dislocate.

516
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,432
How could I kill that woman?

517
00:36:51,432 --> 00:36:53,384
I don't even have the strength.

518
00:36:53,384 --> 00:36:58,067
- Did you sue her?
- I was going to, but the video back then

519
00:36:58,067 --> 00:36:59,720
went viral.

520
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:00,744
Look at this.

521
00:37:00,744 --> 00:37:01,832
[While exercising with Pposong,]
<i>What are you doing?</i>

522
00:37:01,832 --> 00:37:02,984
[an intruder attacked]
<i>We're live right now!</i>

523
00:37:04,072 --> 00:37:05,716
<i>Darn it!</i>

524
00:37:06,790 --> 00:37:08,264
Do you see the views?

525
00:37:08,264 --> 00:37:09,832
It's 2.53 million.

526
00:37:09,832 --> 00:37:13,576
It even hit the trending list.

527
00:37:13,576 --> 00:37:17,672
Did the woman downstairs know

528
00:37:17,672 --> 00:37:19,112
this video was uploaded to NewTube?

529
00:37:19,112 --> 00:37:23,648
Oh, my. If she had known, my left arm
would've been ripped right off.

530
00:37:26,792 --> 00:37:31,048
Ma'am, there might be complaints
from the residents, so at this point...

531
00:37:31,048 --> 00:37:33,480
Should we stop here and leave?

532
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:35,432
Yes, we should be going... Pardon?

533
00:37:35,432 --> 00:37:36,616
You're leaving?

534
00:37:36,616 --> 00:37:39,912
Really? You won't call us again later, right?

535
00:37:39,912 --> 00:37:41,384
Why would I?

536
00:37:41,384 --> 00:37:44,136
We're all busy people. I'll be going now.

537
00:37:44,136 --> 00:37:45,544
Thank you for your hard work!

538
00:37:45,544 --> 00:37:46,952
Take care on your way!

539
00:37:46,952 --> 00:37:49,952
I'll formally introduce myself later.

540
00:37:54,664 --> 00:37:59,040
Yes, it's me. I think there's
nothing to worry about here.

541
00:38:18,120 --> 00:38:20,584
[Rebirth, Yoon Jong Shin]

542
00:38:36,584 --> 00:38:38,568
[Snack and Confection]

543
00:38:38,568 --> 00:38:41,288
[Spicy Pork Lunchbox]

544
00:38:45,192 --> 00:38:47,432
[Spicy Pork Lunchbox]

545
00:40:10,472 --> 00:40:15,048
You always have spicy pork lunchboxes here?
Everywhere else is sold out.

546
00:40:15,048 --> 00:40:17,000
Oh.

547
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:18,952
I see.

548
00:40:18,952 --> 00:40:22,400
Our problem is we always
end up with excess stock.

549
00:40:23,144 --> 00:40:26,152
Well, is there

550
00:40:26,152 --> 00:40:30,880
a lunchbox you'd personally prefer?

551
00:40:38,536 --> 00:40:44,896
Oh, I'm just asking for
market research purposes.

552
00:40:47,144 --> 00:40:49,448
Sweet and sour soy chicken.

553
00:40:49,448 --> 00:40:50,670
Sweet... and sour soy chicken?

554
00:40:50,670 --> 00:40:52,840
You don't have that, do you?

555
00:40:52,840 --> 00:40:55,552
This will do. Please check me out.

556
00:41:08,688 --> 00:41:12,000
[Interior photo, delicious fried dumplings]

557
00:41:29,256 --> 00:41:30,967
[O Ran Chinese Restaurant]

558
00:41:30,967 --> 00:41:34,344
Come on, Jeong Ho Myung.

559
00:41:34,344 --> 00:41:36,672
Get moving.

560
00:41:37,308 --> 00:41:39,360
Please move!

561
00:41:40,442 --> 00:41:42,144
Move!

562
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:47,160
This is refreshing!

563
00:41:57,960 --> 00:41:59,120
You...

564
00:41:59,120 --> 00:42:03,592
Leaving the restaurant every day
for that K-pop or whatever...

565
00:42:03,592 --> 00:42:06,120
Why?

566
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:08,440
You got a problem with it?

567
00:42:08,440 --> 00:42:10,000
No,

568
00:42:10,760 --> 00:42:13,512
I'm not complaining.

569
00:42:13,512 --> 00:42:16,104
Since having Ji Woo, your back
hasn't been great.

570
00:42:16,104 --> 00:42:18,056
I'm just saying this

571
00:42:18,056 --> 00:42:20,232
because I'm worried
you might hurt your back dancing.

572
00:42:20,232 --> 00:42:23,328
Dance is my rehabilitation therapy.
Don't worry about it.

573
00:42:28,136 --> 00:42:33,920
Still, wouldn't it be better to look into
other rehabilitation treatments?

574
00:42:33,920 --> 00:42:36,648
Preferably something that doesn't
affect running the restaurant...

575
00:42:36,648 --> 00:42:38,248
- Dad!
- Huh?

576
00:42:38,248 --> 00:42:41,736
Do you know how much
my dance club helps this restaurant?

577
00:42:41,736 --> 00:42:44,552
When tourism dropped
and sales were cut in half,

578
00:42:44,552 --> 00:42:49,224
don't you remember the members
bringing friends and family here?

579
00:42:49,224 --> 00:42:50,420
Huh?

580
00:42:50,420 --> 00:42:53,660
Oh, so my daughter had such deep intentions.

581
00:42:53,660 --> 00:42:57,184
Then you should keep going.
Keep going, just go.

582
00:43:02,152 --> 00:43:03,784
W-What is this?

583
00:43:03,784 --> 00:43:05,792
Heaven Capital!

584
00:43:06,705 --> 00:43:08,480
Ran a tab?

585
00:43:11,510 --> 00:43:15,656
Dad, didn't I tell you
not to take orders from them?

586
00:43:15,656 --> 00:43:19,656
Well, the idea of selectively
refusing customers

587
00:43:19,656 --> 00:43:22,568
just doesn't sit right with my principles.

588
00:43:22,568 --> 00:43:26,440
I also thought I could collect the overdue
payments at the same time...

589
00:43:26,440 --> 00:43:29,630
So you gave it on credit again?

590
00:43:31,208 --> 00:43:34,248
- Ho Myung said he could collect the tab.
- He said he was confident...

591
00:43:34,248 --> 00:43:37,750
He said he could collect
all the overdue payments too.

592
00:43:37,750 --> 00:43:41,010
When did I ever say that?
Father, you can't say things like that.

593
00:43:41,010 --> 00:43:43,250
Is this really the time
to be giving out credit?

594
00:43:46,790 --> 00:43:48,296
Everyone, listen.

595
00:43:48,296 --> 00:43:50,230
We need to stay sharp.

596
00:43:50,230 --> 00:43:51,400
If we keep going like this,

597
00:43:51,400 --> 00:43:52,990
closing the restaurant
will be just a matter of time.

598
00:43:52,990 --> 00:43:56,850
We're all working hard,
me, your dad, and him too.

599
00:43:56,850 --> 00:43:58,056
I'm working hard as well.

600
00:43:58,056 --> 00:44:00,930
It's not about working hard,
it's about doing it well.

601
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:06,152
At your age, is there
any other job you can do?

602
00:44:06,152 --> 00:44:07,912
There's nothing, right?

603
00:44:07,912 --> 00:44:10,030
We need to build this restaurant up properly,

604
00:44:10,030 --> 00:44:12,751
so when we get older,
we can send Ji Woo to college and all!

605
00:44:12,751 --> 00:44:13,896
- Oh, hold on.
- Hold on.

606
00:44:13,896 --> 00:44:15,936
Oh, seriously...

607
00:44:18,292 --> 00:44:20,800
Just sit!

608
00:44:21,896 --> 00:44:23,400
I'll go throw out the trash.

609
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:25,288
Yeah.

610
00:44:25,288 --> 00:44:27,030
I was going to do that.

611
00:44:27,030 --> 00:44:29,152
- Do it after dinner.
- Mr. Jeong!

612
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:32,200
[Prescription medication guidance]

613
00:45:34,248 --> 00:45:35,912
[Side effects may increase
when drinking alcohol]

614
00:46:07,368 --> 00:46:09,576
[No Signal]

615
00:47:40,100 --> 00:47:41,700
Huh?

616
00:48:36,219 --> 00:48:38,720
[NIS First Deputy Director Han Kyung Wook
uncovered the truth of the case]

617
00:48:38,720 --> 00:48:40,520
NIS.

618
00:48:40,520 --> 00:48:42,200
[Two NIS Agents Missing On Ferry Operation]
Ferry.

619
00:48:42,200 --> 00:48:45,259
[NIS Agent Disappearance
Exposes Lapses in Internal Security]

620
00:48:45,259 --> 00:48:47,260
[Murder of Kwon Sun Bok Linked to Gang Boss]
Kwon Sun Bok.

621
00:48:57,099 --> 00:49:00,140
[Yeongseondo Island]

622
00:49:03,060 --> 00:49:06,440
Yeongseondo Island.

623
00:49:06,440 --> 00:49:09,660
[Yeongseondo Island]

624
00:49:16,379 --> 00:49:17,940
Where is Jeong Ho Myung?

625
00:49:34,619 --> 00:49:39,219
[Don't miss this market day]

626
00:49:41,499 --> 00:49:44,339
[Unbelievable prices,
market day specials you'll regret missing]

627
00:49:55,760 --> 00:49:57,927
<i>You said when you were found
after losing your memory,</i>

628
00:49:57,927 --> 00:50:00,779
<i>you were wearing women's clothes, right?</i>

629
00:50:00,779 --> 00:50:02,297
<i>About those women's clothes,</i>

630
00:50:02,297 --> 00:50:04,980
have you worn them since?

631
00:50:04,980 --> 00:50:07,520
Why would I wear women's clothes?

632
00:50:07,520 --> 00:50:10,040
Instead of denying it outright,

633
00:50:10,040 --> 00:50:13,219
how about trying it once?

634
00:50:14,100 --> 00:50:16,379
Your past gender identity

635
00:50:16,379 --> 00:50:20,000
might be a clue to your memory.

636
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:21,621
<i>Clue.</i>

637
00:50:25,480 --> 00:50:27,480
This looks terrible on me.

638
00:50:29,819 --> 00:50:31,700
- Nam Il!
- Who are you?

639
00:50:31,700 --> 00:50:34,599
- So you came back? Good decision.
- Don't come close, stay back!

640
00:50:37,520 --> 00:50:39,140
What are you wearing?

641
00:50:40,200 --> 00:50:42,360
I'm just trying to recover my memories.

642
00:50:42,360 --> 00:50:44,420
No, no. Stop. Don't say anything.

643
00:50:44,420 --> 00:50:45,600
I don't want to know.

644
00:50:45,600 --> 00:50:47,380
- I'm telling you it's not like that.
- Stay back!

645
00:50:47,380 --> 00:50:50,179
- Listen to me.
- Please, stay back!

646
00:50:54,680 --> 00:50:57,220
- Nam Il, I...
- Say it from there.

647
00:50:57,220 --> 00:50:58,820
Just from there.

648
00:50:59,460 --> 00:51:01,440
You've known me for ten years,
and you still don't know your uncle?

649
00:51:01,440 --> 00:51:03,320
Ugh, stop saying you're my "uncle"

650
00:51:03,320 --> 00:51:04,850
and acting all close.

651
00:51:04,850 --> 00:51:06,320
It's really annoying.

652
00:51:07,659 --> 00:51:11,080
My grandpa took you in out of kindness.

653
00:51:11,080 --> 00:51:12,720
I don't see you as family.

654
00:51:14,020 --> 00:51:16,960
Why would I call some suspicious guy "uncle"?

655
00:51:18,100 --> 00:51:21,401
Alright, let's talk about that later.

656
00:51:21,401 --> 00:51:22,720
Why aren't you going to school?

657
00:51:22,720 --> 00:51:25,240
- And why aren't you coming home?
- Jeez.

658
00:51:26,160 --> 00:51:28,620
Who would want to live in a place like this?

659
00:51:29,620 --> 00:51:32,141
Ugh, if I just hit the slot once properly,

660
00:51:32,141 --> 00:51:34,720
I'd get out of this place, darn it!

661
00:51:34,720 --> 00:51:36,680
Slot?

662
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:38,300
Are you gambling?

663
00:51:39,960 --> 00:51:41,860
What?

664
00:51:41,860 --> 00:51:43,480
Why?

665
00:51:44,120 --> 00:51:46,640
Hey, Heo Nam Il! Aren't you coming out?

666
00:51:46,640 --> 00:51:48,320
Anyway, stay out of my business.

667
00:51:48,320 --> 00:51:49,500
Hey, Nam Il! Where are you going?

668
00:51:49,500 --> 00:51:50,740
Let's talk. Oh, my.

669
00:51:50,740 --> 00:51:52,900
Oh, my knee... Nam Il!

670
00:51:52,900 --> 00:51:54,680
Where are you going?

671
00:51:54,680 --> 00:51:57,140
Where are you going? Huh?

672
00:51:57,140 --> 00:51:58,779
At least put your pants on. Darn it.

673
00:52:05,160 --> 00:52:06,780
No way...

674
00:52:21,880 --> 00:52:23,960
That punk took the house deed.

675
00:52:31,592 --> 00:52:34,696
Click, click, click!

676
00:52:34,696 --> 00:52:36,616
Come on!

677
00:52:38,024 --> 00:52:40,584
Jeez, come on!

678
00:52:40,584 --> 00:52:43,628
Just say so if you don't want to sell.

679
00:52:52,440 --> 00:52:54,120
Give me one.

680
00:52:56,000 --> 00:52:57,600
Would you like it in a cone?

681
00:53:08,168 --> 00:53:09,544
Click!

682
00:53:11,048 --> 00:53:12,078
Click!

683
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:13,760
Click!

684
00:53:13,760 --> 00:53:15,120
Stop messing around.

685
00:53:15,120 --> 00:53:17,320
Come on, come on!

686
00:53:17,320 --> 00:53:19,120
Click! Click!

687
00:53:19,120 --> 00:53:20,899
- Jeez!
- Clack!

688
00:53:20,899 --> 00:53:22,888
Again!

689
00:53:22,888 --> 00:53:24,968
- Click!
- Uh, jeez!

690
00:53:24,968 --> 00:53:26,440
Alright.

691
00:53:31,560 --> 00:53:32,639
What's the occasion?

692
00:53:32,639 --> 00:53:34,440
It's not even the day for a meet-up.

693
00:53:34,440 --> 00:53:36,340
Meet-up?

694
00:53:36,340 --> 00:53:39,040
Since when did a meet-up
mean a scheduled meeting?

695
00:53:40,299 --> 00:53:43,739
You've gotten more and more relaxed
since you got married.

696
00:53:43,739 --> 00:53:45,380
We've been waiting for 10 years.

697
00:53:45,380 --> 00:53:47,220
How can anyone stay sharp?

698
00:53:47,220 --> 00:53:50,440
Stop nagging and get to the point. I'm busy.

699
00:53:50,440 --> 00:53:52,680
You know Black Pearl, right?

700
00:53:52,680 --> 00:53:54,280
Black Pearl?

701
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:57,720
- Did you find her?
- Found her.

702
00:54:00,240 --> 00:54:01,757
Since that day 10 years ago,

703
00:54:01,757 --> 00:54:05,020
she was hiding in a villa in Imcheon City.

704
00:54:08,100 --> 00:54:11,339
- Why was she hiding in South Korea?
- No idea.

705
00:54:11,339 --> 00:54:14,520
Maybe she was looking for the item like us.

706
00:54:17,300 --> 00:54:20,680
- So did you find anything?
- Nothing.

707
00:54:20,680 --> 00:54:22,779
She was found dead.

708
00:54:22,779 --> 00:54:26,900
- What?
- Officially suicide. I suspect homicide.

709
00:54:26,900 --> 00:54:28,753
I think her location got exposed

710
00:54:28,753 --> 00:54:31,040
when this video was uploaded to NewTube.

711
00:54:32,360 --> 00:54:34,980
It can't be the North's doing at this point.

712
00:54:36,080 --> 00:54:38,020
- It's Han Kyung Wook, right?
- No, we don't know yet.

713
00:54:38,020 --> 00:54:41,020
Come on, do you think Han Kyung Wook
would just leave his past alone?

714
00:54:45,360 --> 00:54:47,480
We shouldn't just sit here anymore.

715
00:54:47,480 --> 00:54:51,080
- Shouldn't we start taking action?
- No, it's still too early.

716
00:54:52,059 --> 00:54:54,240
<i>A prosecutor has caught wind of this case.</i>

717
00:54:54,240 --> 00:54:55,976
[Construction Registration Company]
<i>I'm keeping an eye on her,</i>

718
00:54:55,976 --> 00:54:56,980
<i>so just wait a bit more.</i>

719
00:54:56,980 --> 00:54:58,360
- Seong Wo!
- Come on.

720
00:54:58,360 --> 00:55:00,580
Don't you know how high
Han Kyung Wook has climbed?

721
00:55:00,580 --> 00:55:02,745
If we act rashly
and our position gets exposed,

722
00:55:02,745 --> 00:55:04,619
man, that's really the end for us.

723
00:55:04,619 --> 00:55:06,500
So we're just going to stay idle like this?

724
00:55:06,500 --> 00:55:07,700
Aren't you frustrated at all?

725
00:55:07,700 --> 00:55:10,400
Then go find out
where Bulgae and the item are.

726
00:55:10,400 --> 00:55:11,961
I've been saying this all along!

727
00:55:11,961 --> 00:55:14,051
If Bulgae and the item were
on Yeongseondo Island,

728
00:55:14,051 --> 00:55:15,360
we would've found them long ago.

729
00:55:15,360 --> 00:55:19,260
The receiver's broken, and Bulgae
fell into the sea that day and died!

730
00:55:19,260 --> 00:55:20,920
Ho Myung!

731
00:55:21,979 --> 00:55:25,360
Seong Wo, let's do something
before more time passes, okay?

732
00:55:25,360 --> 00:55:26,961
I...

733
00:55:27,700 --> 00:55:29,320
I was...

734
00:55:33,780 --> 00:55:35,980
diagnosed with menopause recently.

735
00:55:37,200 --> 00:55:39,320
So this whining

736
00:55:39,320 --> 00:55:43,019
and mood swings are...

737
00:55:43,019 --> 00:55:44,201
your menopause symptoms?

738
00:55:44,201 --> 00:55:45,920
Jeez, I don't know.

739
00:55:46,660 --> 00:55:49,800
Sometimes I feel completely drained,
and other times I feel anxious for no reason.

740
00:55:49,800 --> 00:55:52,139
The hospital prescribed me
some hormone medication,

741
00:55:52,139 --> 00:55:54,040
but it doesn't really seem to help.

742
00:55:54,040 --> 00:55:55,780
Seong Wo.

743
00:55:56,619 --> 00:55:58,360
We don't have time.

744
00:55:58,360 --> 00:56:00,000
If this keeps going,

745
00:56:00,000 --> 00:56:01,819
I really...

746
00:56:01,819 --> 00:56:05,140
I feel like I won't be able to do anything!

747
00:56:19,304 --> 00:56:23,560
[Ji Woo's Kindergarten Pickup]
Oh, you have to pick up the kid?

748
00:56:23,560 --> 00:56:25,160
Go quickly.

749
00:56:26,139 --> 00:56:28,520
Hurry, I'll call you later. Go.

750
00:56:46,360 --> 00:56:51,219
[Happy Kindergarten]
Goodbye! There you go.

751
00:56:51,219 --> 00:56:54,216
- Let's take the bus!
- Come on!

752
00:56:59,339 --> 00:57:01,288
[Andrew's English Class]

753
00:57:13,680 --> 00:57:17,040
- Ji Woo!
- Oh, Dad.

754
00:57:18,960 --> 00:57:21,320
Do you want me to send you
to an academy too, Ji Woo?

755
00:57:21,320 --> 00:57:22,539
No way.

756
00:57:22,539 --> 00:57:24,299
If I want to go to an academy,

757
00:57:24,299 --> 00:57:27,460
you and Mom would have to sell
a hundred bowls of jjajang noodles.

758
00:57:27,460 --> 00:57:28,560
Why are you worrying about that?

759
00:57:28,560 --> 00:57:30,340
I can just sell a hundred bowls.

760
00:57:30,340 --> 00:57:32,180
That would be hard on you, Dad.

761
00:57:32,180 --> 00:57:33,830
It's fine.

762
00:57:42,020 --> 00:57:43,620
Dad.

763
00:57:49,300 --> 00:57:51,060
Do you want me

764
00:57:51,060 --> 00:57:52,720
to give you this?

765
00:57:57,380 --> 00:57:58,420
Oh, this is

766
00:57:58,420 --> 00:58:01,060
your favorite Kamen Rider.

767
00:58:01,060 --> 00:58:02,060
Yeah.

768
00:58:02,060 --> 00:58:05,160
This gives me energy when I wear it.

769
00:58:05,160 --> 00:58:07,200
Dad, you should stay strong too.

770
00:58:09,280 --> 00:58:10,900
Let's go!

771
00:58:41,060 --> 00:58:43,180
Welcome...

772
00:58:48,299 --> 00:58:50,119
Hello.

773
00:58:51,000 --> 00:58:53,280
Same as always?

774
00:59:02,580 --> 00:59:04,100
- Dad.
- Yeah.

775
00:59:04,100 --> 00:59:05,960
That "Oldboy" guy is here.

776
00:59:05,960 --> 00:59:08,139
That dumpling guy?

777
00:59:08,139 --> 00:59:10,000
Haven't seen him in a while.

778
00:59:12,900 --> 00:59:14,500
Oh, my.

779
00:59:22,299 --> 00:59:23,899
Welcome!

780
00:59:25,380 --> 00:59:27,400
Let's talk for a second.

781
00:59:28,840 --> 00:59:30,480
What is it?

782
00:59:32,160 --> 00:59:34,619
Let's send Ji Woo

783
00:59:34,619 --> 00:59:36,279
to this academy.

784
00:59:37,440 --> 00:59:39,592
[Andrew's English Class]

785
00:59:41,419 --> 00:59:42,920
Ah, never mind.

786
00:59:42,920 --> 00:59:45,040
We don't even have money.
What academy are you talking about?

787
00:59:45,040 --> 00:59:46,400
Let's send him when he gets a little older.

788
00:59:46,400 --> 00:59:48,000
Kwon O Ran.

789
00:59:48,000 --> 00:59:49,499
Can't we do this one thing for him?

790
00:59:49,499 --> 00:59:51,290
All of Ji Woo's friends are attending there.

791
00:59:51,290 --> 00:59:52,820
I want to send him too.

792
00:59:52,820 --> 00:59:54,699
But can you even afford it?

793
00:59:54,699 --> 00:59:56,899
You can't even properly
increase the restaurant's sales.

794
01:00:07,940 --> 01:00:10,880
We'll serve you with dedication.
This is O Ran Chinese Restaurant.

795
01:00:11,819 --> 01:00:13,438
Pardon?

796
01:00:16,200 --> 01:00:18,459
Understood.

797
01:00:19,710 --> 01:00:21,560
Delivery? Where to?

798
01:00:21,560 --> 01:00:24,200
- Heaven Capital.
- Heaven Capital?

799
01:00:24,939 --> 01:00:26,299
I told you not to take orders from there.

800
01:00:26,299 --> 01:00:27,300
Why?

801
01:00:27,300 --> 01:00:28,960
Isn't it good for sales?

802
01:00:28,960 --> 01:00:30,779
I can handle all the credit payments.

803
01:00:30,779 --> 01:00:34,219
Come on, how would you
possibly collect those debts?

804
01:00:34,219 --> 01:00:35,249
You go.

805
01:00:35,249 --> 01:00:36,459
Oh, okay, you go.

806
01:00:36,459 --> 01:00:37,560
Why? I'm not going, not going.

807
01:00:37,560 --> 01:00:39,010
Why not? You go!

808
01:00:39,010 --> 01:00:40,920
Why are you making me do it?
Just send Ho Myung.

809
01:00:40,920 --> 01:00:42,060
You can go yourself.

810
01:00:42,060 --> 01:00:44,250
I keep saying I don't want to go.
Why do you keep trying to send me?

811
01:00:44,250 --> 01:00:45,630
You said you'd go last time.

812
01:00:45,630 --> 01:00:47,859
I said I'm going!

813
01:00:53,120 --> 01:00:55,019
I'll get

814
01:00:55,019 --> 01:00:57,680
all the money back from the tabs!

815
01:00:57,680 --> 01:00:58,779
Just watch me.

816
01:00:58,779 --> 01:01:01,220
See if I can do it or not.

817
01:01:01,220 --> 01:01:03,200
Just watch me.

818
01:01:03,200 --> 01:01:04,820
<i>Those eyes</i>

819
01:01:04,820 --> 01:01:07,859
<i>aren't the lifeless eyes
of a Chinese restaurant owner.</i>

820
01:01:10,960 --> 01:01:13,380
<i>They're the eyes of an NIS agent I saw</i>

821
01:01:13,380 --> 01:01:15,560
<i>10 years ago on a ferry.</i>

822
01:01:16,980 --> 01:01:18,280
[Origin Label]

823
01:01:41,400 --> 01:01:43,880
- Nice to meet you!
- Oh, yes, it's fine.

824
01:02:07,099 --> 01:02:08,699
Jeez.

825
01:02:09,860 --> 01:02:11,460
That punk...

826
01:02:24,379 --> 01:02:26,260
Where is the house deed?

827
01:02:26,260 --> 01:02:28,200
The house deed?

828
01:02:28,200 --> 01:02:30,740
- What about it?
- Don't you know what kind of house that is?

829
01:02:30,740 --> 01:02:33,540
That's the house
your grandfather built himself!

830
01:02:33,540 --> 01:02:35,200
So what if he built it himself?

831
01:02:35,200 --> 01:02:38,340
The main beams are rotten,
and it's just a matter of when it collapses.

832
01:02:38,340 --> 01:02:40,740
Better make use of it before it goes down.

833
01:02:40,740 --> 01:02:42,440
Don't tell me...

834
01:02:43,800 --> 01:02:44,800
Jeez.

835
01:02:44,800 --> 01:02:47,240
I thought of it as a gift
from my grandfather in heaven

836
01:02:47,240 --> 01:02:48,880
and cashed it right away, so what?

837
01:02:48,880 --> 01:02:50,619
No way, you're lying...

838
01:02:50,619 --> 01:02:51,800
Seriously.

839
01:02:51,800 --> 01:02:53,939
Don't jinx it. Darn it.

840
01:02:54,820 --> 01:02:57,140
If that hits once,
it pays a hundred times over.

841
01:02:57,140 --> 01:02:58,920
If it hits,

842
01:02:58,920 --> 01:03:01,800
I'll buy you a brand-new apartment,

843
01:03:01,800 --> 01:03:03,280
so just sit back and watch, alright?

844
01:03:03,280 --> 01:03:05,720
Get yourself together, come on!

845
01:03:09,220 --> 01:03:10,760
[Heaven Capital]

846
01:03:10,760 --> 01:03:12,960
You cashed it over there, right?

847
01:03:12,960 --> 01:03:16,170
I'll go get it back, so just wait here.

848
01:03:17,800 --> 01:03:20,539
If you go there, you'll die!

849
01:03:20,539 --> 01:03:22,139
Darn it.

850
01:03:30,980 --> 01:03:32,500
Yeah, come on in.

851
01:03:32,500 --> 01:03:33,739
You're good to go.

852
01:03:33,739 --> 01:03:36,220
Win big.

853
01:03:37,900 --> 01:03:40,500
So, how can I help you?

854
01:03:40,500 --> 01:03:44,360
My nephew pawned a house deed for a loan.
I mean, because of that...

855
01:03:45,460 --> 01:03:47,099
I'll repay the money.

856
01:03:47,099 --> 01:03:49,240
- That house must never be sold.
- Oh.

857
01:03:49,240 --> 01:03:51,320
- So, you've come to get the house deed back?
- Yes.

858
01:03:51,320 --> 01:03:52,960
Yeah, have a seat.

859
01:03:56,560 --> 01:03:58,200
The interest?

860
01:03:59,840 --> 01:04:01,321
He said he just borrowed it.

861
01:04:01,321 --> 01:04:03,800
Oh, just now! How long has it been?

862
01:04:03,800 --> 01:04:05,060
One hour, two hours...

863
01:04:05,060 --> 01:04:06,880
One hour, two hours... let me see.

864
01:04:06,880 --> 01:04:10,240
Then, for one hour, it's 3.6 million won.

865
01:04:10,240 --> 01:04:13,200
For two hours, it's 7.2 million won!

866
01:04:13,200 --> 01:04:15,520
What, he just borrowed it,
and the interest is 7.2 million won already?

867
01:04:15,520 --> 01:04:18,080
If you borrowed money,
you need to pay the interest!

868
01:04:18,080 --> 01:04:20,920
Isn't all of this illegal? Right?

869
01:04:20,920 --> 01:04:23,360
Darn it, what illegal stuff
are you even talking about here?

870
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:24,360
Huh?

871
01:04:24,360 --> 01:04:27,339
Give it to me. I need to take that deed.

872
01:04:27,339 --> 01:04:28,859
Ugh, ouch...

873
01:04:28,859 --> 01:04:32,480
Jeez, why are there so many
troublemakers these days?

874
01:04:32,480 --> 01:04:35,048
Sir, get up, come on.

875
01:04:36,640 --> 01:04:38,259
Sir.

876
01:04:39,019 --> 01:04:40,480
If you borrowed money,

877
01:04:40,480 --> 01:04:42,020
you should

878
01:04:42,020 --> 01:04:43,720
pay interest, right?

879
01:04:43,720 --> 01:04:45,360
I just need the deed.

880
01:04:45,360 --> 01:04:46,760
Darn it.

881
01:04:46,760 --> 01:04:48,360
Ugh!

882
01:04:49,080 --> 01:04:50,859
Withdraw the gambling industry!

883
01:04:50,859 --> 01:04:53,200
- Withdraw! Withdraw!
- Withdraw! Withdraw!

884
01:04:53,200 --> 01:04:57,440
A casino in pristine Yeongseondo Island?
What nonsense is that!

885
01:05:12,600 --> 01:05:15,816
[O Ran Chinese Restaurant, Chinese Cuisine]

886
01:05:26,580 --> 01:05:27,580
Jeez.

887
01:05:27,580 --> 01:05:28,859
What, is he dead?

888
01:05:28,859 --> 01:05:31,120
Hey, hey, quickly help him up.

889
01:05:31,120 --> 01:05:32,400
Sir!

890
01:05:32,400 --> 01:05:34,980
Go sleep at home.

891
01:05:34,980 --> 01:05:36,240
Don't retreat!

892
01:05:36,240 --> 01:05:39,100
Soldiers of the republic are never weak!

893
01:05:45,620 --> 01:05:46,660
Right, right.

894
01:05:46,660 --> 01:05:48,580
Quickly get up and defeat the enemies!

895
01:05:48,580 --> 01:05:52,440
I'll certainly execute
the enemies of the republic.

896
01:05:52,440 --> 01:05:54,200
Jeez, wake up. Wake up!

897
01:05:54,200 --> 01:05:55,940
Come on, wake up.

898
01:05:55,940 --> 01:05:57,880
I said go sleep at home.

899
01:06:05,360 --> 01:06:07,340
Huh? What's with his eyes?

900
01:06:14,568 --> 01:06:15,976
What's going on?

901
01:06:19,340 --> 01:06:21,400
- What's with that guy?
- What?

902
01:06:25,400 --> 01:06:27,000
Huh?

903
01:06:54,088 --> 01:06:55,432
You little punk!

904
01:07:44,820 --> 01:07:46,721
<i>Finally found him.</i>

905
01:07:47,650 --> 01:07:49,299
<i>Bulgae.</i>

906
01:08:10,040 --> 01:08:11,400
That guy made a move, I'm telling you.

907
01:08:11,400 --> 01:08:13,480
It's the guy we've been watching
for 10 years.

908
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:15,320
He's not an ordinary civilian, right?

909
01:08:15,320 --> 01:08:16,821
007 agent.

910
01:08:16,821 --> 01:08:20,939
I've made sure she won't get
anywhere near the case again.

911
01:08:20,939 --> 01:08:22,792
This is a special service for regulars.

912
01:08:22,792 --> 01:08:24,020
Are you crazy?

913
01:08:24,020 --> 01:08:25,819
Did I go out and mess around like you?

914
01:08:25,819 --> 01:08:28,618
You started all this over a noise complaint?

915
01:08:28,618 --> 01:08:30,120
I'd like to ask you a favor.

916
01:08:30,120 --> 01:08:35,060
If Jeong Ho Myung's respected senior,
Mr. Cho Seong Wo, is said to be dead,

917
01:08:35,060 --> 01:08:38,299
he will definitely show up at the funeral.

918
01:08:38,299 --> 01:08:39,540
Boss!

919
01:08:39,540 --> 01:08:41,658
Now it's confirmed.
